The paper discusses the impact of batch normalization on the behavior of deep convolution networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also explores the effect of batch structure on the performance of the network, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of labels in test batches, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL).
